cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.AR

This paper discusses a methodology for identifying similar or identical code fragments in binary programs, which is relevant to the fields of software engineering and security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions the challenge of detecting similar binary code across architectures, which suggests the category cs.AR (Architecture). The methodology proposed in the paper involves executing and emulating functions, which relates to categories cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Lastly, the paper discusses the trade-off between comparison accuracy and coverage, which is a topic in category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
